info.author: Paul Harrison
info.description:
A re-implementation of the C "Vanilla-Snob" MML
        mixture-modeller by Chris Wallace. Little Snob is a
        library for unsupervised classification of a set of data
        into classes. It can handle continuous or discrete data,
        and is capable of determining the optimal number of classes
        to use on its own.
info.name: Little-Snob
info.summary: A simple library for unsupervised classification of data.
info.html_description:
A re-implementation of the C “Vanilla-Snob” MML
mixture-modeller by Chris Wallace. Little Snob is a library for unsupervised classification of a set of data into classes. It can handle continuous or discrete data, and is capable of determining the optimal number of classes to use on its own.
